==English==
===Etymology===
From French ''[[démocrate]]'', from ''[[démocratie]]'' (modelled on ''[[aristocrate]]'' ‘aristocrat’).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈdɛməkræt/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A supporter of [[democracy]]; an advocate of democratic politics (originally as opposed to the [[aristocrats]] in Revolutionary France).

# A supporter of individual responsibility; however, one who realizes individuals are unique and endowed with different characterstics beyond the individual's control.  

